<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: CAMARILLO; 
</P>
<P>
EXPLOSIONS DAMAGE HOUSE, MOBILE HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERRY BRAILO SPENCER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two explosions at a house in a remote area of Camarillo on Monday caused 
extensive damage to the house and minor damage to an adjacent mobile home, fire 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Residents Marjorie and Mario Martinez were inside the house when they heard two 
blasts and discovered flames at the back of the house. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials believe that the fire may have been caused by a propane tank 
explosion. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters were hampered in fighting the blaze because of winds of 20 m.p.h. 
and a lack of water on the property. Water had to be brought in by truck. 
</P>
<P>
There was no estimate of damage, but fire officials said there were many 17th- 
and 18th-Century antiques inside the house. Also on the property was a 1965 
Buick, which had recently been restored. The car was destroyed. GERRY BRAILO 
SPENCER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Firefighter battles house fire in a remote area of Camarillo. MARILYN 
WEISS / For The Times; Photo, John Wade comforts resident Mario Martinez, below 
right. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
