<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
$1 HIKES IN MONTHLY TRASH FEES APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some Simi Valley residents will have to pay about $1 more a month in trash 
collection fees under a plan approved Monday night by the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
The council approved the rate hike requests from American-Simi Rubbish Co. and 
Anderson Rubbish Co. following a public hearing. 
</P>
<P>
An annual hearing is required to evaluate service and to consider any proposed 
rate increases or other changes in the companies' contracts with the city. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements approved Monday, American-Simi Rubbish, which serves about 
24,000 customers, will be allowed to raise its monthly rate from $13 to $14.10. 
Its senior citizen rate will increase from $10.20 a month to $11.05 a month. 
</P>
<P>
Anderson Rubbish, which serves 2,000 customers, will increase its monthly rate 
from $13 to $14.05, while senior citizen rates will jump from $10.20 a month to 
$11.05. 
</P>
<P>
The trash haulers cited increased fuel costs and increases in tipping fees at 
the Simi Valley landfill as the primary reasons for the rate hikes. Dumping 
fees will increase from $30.10 to $34.60 per ton beginning Jan. 1. CARLOS V. 
LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
