METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SANTA CLARITA HIRES FULL-TIME LOBBYIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michael Murphy, administrative aide to Assemblywoman Cathie Wright (R-Simi 
Valley) for seven years, has been hired as a full-time lobbyist by Santa 
Clarita, city officials announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
As the city's first governmental affairs officer, Murphy will represent Santa 
Clarita before area, state and federal governments, City Manager George 
Caravalho said. Murphy's job will include handling development and 
transportation issues and lobbying against plans by Los Angeles County to open 
garbage dumps near the city in Towsley and Elsmere canyons. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy, a Simi Valley resident, will begin work Dec. 19 with an annual salary 
of $43,440. The council had hired a lobbying firm, Capital Representation 
Group, for $5,000 a month last year but fired the company in September. 
