<HEADLINE>
<P>
NCAA ACCEPTS MARYLAND PENALTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLLEGE PARK, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The NCAA has accepted Maryland's self-imposed penalties for basketball Coach 
Gary Williams and some staff members watching a preseason pickup game last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
The penalties were also for issuing practice gear during the summer of 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Maryland reprimanded those involved in the NCAA violations and postponed 
preseason practice by five days to Oct. 20., according to the university. 
</P>
<P>
The letter from NCAA Assistant Director of Enforcement David Berst stated, "The 
committee (NCAA Committee on Infractions) has accepted the university's actions 
as appropriate in this matter and concluded that no additional penalty should 
be imposed by the committee." 
</P>
</TEXT>
