<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Free agent right-hander Eric Show, 6-8 for the San Diego Padres last season, 
agreed to a two-year contract with the Oakland Athletics. 
</P>
<P>
Show, 35, is 100-87 lifetime in 10 major league seasons, all with the Padres. 
His best season was in 1988, when he was 16-11 with a 3.26 ERA. Show made 12 
starts and 27 relief appearances in 1990, compiling an earned-run average of 
5.76. 
</P>
<P>
Show made $800,000 in 1990 in the final season of a two-year deal worth $2.5 
million. Terms of the agreement with the A's were not disclosed. 
