<P>
Feldman on Probation: Actor Corey Feldman was sentenced Monday to four years' 
probation and fined $5,000 in a plea bargain related to two drug possession 
arrests. 
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old pleaded no contest to two charges of heroin possession and one 
of cocaine possession. In exchange, prosecutors agreed to dismiss felony 
charges of heroin possession for sale and transportation of heroin. Feldman 
agreed to finish a seven-month drug rehabilitation program, which he entered in 
October. While in the program, the actor will be barred from working in the 
entertainment industry. BETH KLEID 
