<TEXT>
<P>
Eagle-Picher Asbestos Suits Consolidated: U.S. District Judge Jack B. Weinstein 
said he will create a class action consolidating 65,000 asbestos injury claims 
against Eagle-Picher Industries Inc. Attorneys for the victims said they would 
fight Weinstein's attempts to consolidate the cases, saying the company's 
$625-million long-term settlement plan is not enough. Weinstein faces an 
additional roadblock in the form of a petition filed Monday in U.S. Bankruptcy 
Court in Cincinnati seeking to force the Cincinnati-based industrial products 
manufacturer involuntarily into bankruptcy proceedings. Under federal law, the 
bankruptcy petition puts all other court action on hold. 
</P>
