</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OPEC Meeting Will Begin: Ministers of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting 
Countries arrived in Vienna for talks that are likely to leave intact a boost 
in oil production approved last August after Iraq invaded Kuwait. This is 
OPEC's annual winter meeting, which begins Wednesday and is normally used to 
map out production and pricing plans for the coming year. But this year members 
will examine various scenarios for the future so they will be prepared to act 
once the Persian Gulf standoff ends. 
</P>
