<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Eric Bailey and Jeffrey A. Perlman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GIMME REWRITE: "I am not a journalist," says John Wayne Airport Manager Jan 
Mittermeier, above, but there's her article in the current California County, 
the magazine for county supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
It's the rosiest account yet of the how the airport's "state of the art," 
"absolutely distinctive" new "dream terminal" was built. . . . The article 
reports the project's cost without mentioning it was nearly $20 million over 
original estimates. No mention either of bitter disputes with the contractor 
that delayed opening day for five months. "I thought someone would like to see 
something positive for a change," she said. Eric Bailey and Jeffrey A. Perlman 
</P>
</TEXT>
