<P>
PUN POWER: Meanwhile, over on I-5, the latest weapon against congestion is a 
jar of Knott's boysenberry jam. . . . At the transit district's request, 
Knott's donated 600 1.3-ounce jars, which were relabeled "I-5 Traffic Jam" and 
sent them to transportation coordinators at the county's larger companies. 
"Help the I-5 out of a jam. Rideshare," says the accompanying card. . . . The 
idea is to promote the district's new offer of free gasoline to I-5 
car-poolers, and initial reaction has been good, a spokeswoman says. Eric 
Bailey and Jeffrey A. Perlman 
</P>
