<P>
KEEPING WATCH: The surveillance cameras going up on the San Diego Freeway in 
Irvine will be watching for car-pool lane violations, but no one's going to get 
a ticket, says Caltrans. It's to test the experimental design of the car-pool 
lanes between Jeffrey Road and Irvine Center Drive. . . . Along that stretch, a 
"buffer lane" allows motorists to ease between the car-pool and regular lanes. 
It's the only such design in the nation so far. Eric Bailey and Jeffrey A. 
Perlman 
</P>
