<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
FAIR BOARD VOTES FOR NEW BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Fair Board last week approved its 1991 budget and voted to 
spend $6.5 million in reserve funds for a multipurpose building. 
</P>
<P>
The new structure will be near the Arlington Theater on North West Street, 
inside the fairgrounds complex in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Operating revenues for 1991 are expected to total more than $14.3 million, a 1% 
increase over 1990. Operating expenses for the upcoming season were estimated 
at $12.2 million, a 3% increase from the previous year. It is expected that 
operating net income for 1990 will total more than $2.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
The new budget includes plans to spend 12% more on fair attractions, 13% more 
on exhibits, 12% more on administrative expenses and 37% less on equipment than 
1990. 
</P>
