OLYMPIC CLUB TO OPEN ITS DOORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 130-year-old, all-male Olympic Club today tentatively settled a 1987 
discrimination suit with the city by agreeing to admit women and adopting a 
policy of non-discrimination against minorities and women. 
</P>
<P>
In exchange, the city agreed to drop its lawsuit against the club and give it 
an option to buy 17 acres of city land, part of which contains three holes of 
the club's championship golf course. 
</P>
<P>
The Olympic Club, with 6,000 members, agreed to admit women within 60 days, 
adopt the non-discrimination policy and keep in place an existing court 
injunction against discrimination. 
</P>
